RSS Reader for Scraping Data
The reader.py script allows you to scrape RSS feed data from a specified URL.

It provides flexibility to generate the output in either JSON format or a standard format
(e.g., plain text or XML). This tool is especially useful for parsing and extracting structured
data from RSS feeds for further processing or analysis.


Examples of Usage in Command Line

Output in JSON Format:
   python reader.py --json https://news.yahoo.com/rss
This generates the output in JSON format.

Output in Standard Format:
   python reader.py https://news.yahoo.com/rss
This generates the output in a standard format, such as plain text or XML.